You are missing a `createDeck()` call in your `main()` method:

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        createDeck();
        shuffleDeck(deck);
    }

Because the following statement only initializes the `deck` array with `52` `null` values:

    public static String[]deck = new String[52];

You need to fill the `deck` array with actual values to display them properly. And you can safely mark `createDeck()` as `void` because you don&#39;t need to return `deck` array as it is declared as `static` which will be accessible anyway. Same is the case with `shuffleDeck()` method, you don&#39;t need to pass the `static` array, it will be accessible.

Or you could go with another approach in which `deck` array is declared as a local variable and it is passed to these methods as an argument.

